The paper deals with the problem of reconfiguring graph partitions under certain operations, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of gerrymandering detection also involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the algorithms presented in the paper involve computational optimization (cs.SI).
